{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592934","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592934"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:20:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:20:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15288"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15288","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15288"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.68,0.05,0,0,0.26]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7979"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80807"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7979","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7979"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15288"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66127"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19412"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27613"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80807","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80807"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAlcoholic liver disease is a progressive condition that develops through several pathological stages.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a direct consequence of chronic alcohol consumption on the liver?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased albumin synthesis","Enhanced glycogen storage","Increased bile production","Improved lipid metabolism","Portal hypertension"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EChronic alcohol consumption leads to progressive liver damage that ultimately results in \u003Cstrong\u003Eportal hypertension\u003C/strong\u003E. This occurs due to fibrosis and architectural distortion of the liver, causing increased resistance to portal blood flow.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased albumin synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E is a late finding in severe liver disease but is not a direct effect of alcohol. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased bile production\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur with alcoholic liver disease; bile production may actually decrease. \u003Cstrong\u003EEnhanced glycogen storage\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as alcohol actually depletes glycogen stores. \u003Cstrong\u003EImproved lipid metabolism\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as alcohol impairs lipid metabolism, leading to fatty liver.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe progression of alcoholic liver disease typically follows three stages:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EFatty liver (steatosis)\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EAlcoholic hepatitis\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003ECirrhosis with portal hypertension\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Alcoholic liver disease progresses through three main stages: fatty liver (steatosis), alcoholic hepatitis, and cirrhosis","Chronic alcohol consumption causes fat accumulation, inflammation, and eventual fibrosis in hepatocytes","Portal hypertension is a major complication of advanced alcoholic liver disease"],"references":["Torbenson M, Washington K. Pathology of liver disease: advances in the last 50 years. Hum Pathol. 2020 Jan;95:78-98. doi: 10.1016/j.humpath.2019.08.023. Epub 2019 Sep 4. PMID: 31493428","Chan WK, Chuah KH, Rajaram RB, Lim LL, Ratnasingam J, Vethakkan SR. Metabolic Dysfunction-Associated Steatotic Liver Disease (MASLD): A State-of-the-Art Review. J Obes Metab Syndr. 2023 Sep 30;32(3):197-213. doi: 10.7570/jomes23052. Epub 2023 Sep 13. PMID: 37700494; PMCID: PMC10583766","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66127"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15288"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66127"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-23T09:10:06+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-23T09:10:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7979"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80807"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying a